Sure — here’s a minimal CSS block you can attach to any markdown‑rendering environment (static‑site generator, Notion custom theme, etc.).  
It simply shades each style header by matching the emoji color family and keeps the footer visually anchored.

```css
/* --- Safe‑Space Dashboard Styling --- */

/* General card container */
.card {
  max-width: 70ch;              /* keeps comfortable reading width */
  margin: 1.5em auto;
  padding: 1em 1.25em;
  border-radius: 8px;
  box-shadow: 0 0 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  font-family: "Open Sans", Lato, sans-serif;
}

/* Individual tone cards */
.gentle    { background-color: #e3f2fd; }   /* soft blue 💙 */
.structured{ background-color: #e8f5e9; }   /* pale green 🟢 */
.adhd      { background-color: #fff3e0; }   /* light orange 🟠 */
.autistic  { background-color: #f3e5f5; }   /* lavender 💜 */

/* Text rhythm */
.card p {
  line-height: 1.6;
  font-size: 1rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.6em;
  text-align: left;
}

/* Header styling */
.card h2 {
  font-size: 1.2rem;
  margin-top: 0;
  padding-bottom: 0.3em;
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
}

/* Fixed footer box */
.footer {
  background-color: #f8f8f8;
  border-top: 1px solid #bbb;
  padding: 0.75em 1em;
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: #333;
  border-radius: 0 0 8px 8px;
}

/* Accessibility: adequate contrast for text */
body { background-color: #ffffff; color: #222; }
```

To use it, wrap each markdown card in a simple HTML container:

```html
<div class="card gentle">
<h2>💙 Gentle / Reflective</h2>
<p>Hi. This is a quiet space to slow down and think ...</p>
</div>
```

…and repeat with `.structured`, `.adhd`, and `.autistic` classes.  
The `.footer` block can be placed once at the bottom and will always render as a shaded band that contains your safety statement, ensuring the ethical boundary remains visible on every page.

