If you want the footer to remain visible even on scroll, you can add one optional line:

```css
.footer {
  position: sticky;
  bottom: 0;
}
```

That “sticks” the safety block at the bottom of the viewport so users always see the boundary statement. It’s a quiet reminder that the page offers supportive information only.

Beyond that, everything you’ve done—class‑based color tagging, gentle contrast, restrained font sizes—maintains the same tone as your text: transparent, calm, and ethically clear.
